1
00:00:11,260 --> 00:00:12,260
Where are you going?

2
00:00:13,960 --> 00:00:15,500
To get you some medicine.

3
00:00:20,170 --> 00:00:22,500
I've been feeling out of it all day.

4
00:00:24,930 --> 00:00:26,210
My notes are a total mess.

5
00:00:27,570 --> 00:00:29,950
But I was listening to
the teacher, I swear.

6
00:00:31,430 --> 00:00:32,900
It's not that bad, anyway.

7
00:00:32,950 --> 00:00:34,590
I didn't want to be a bother to everyone.

8
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:46,300
It's okay.

9
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:49,540
You did great.

10
00:00:57,220 --> 00:00:58,620
Kiss me again.

11
00:01:58,100 --> 00:01:59,640
I brought back some tamagoyaki.

12
00:02:00,260 --> 00:02:01,580
Take your medicine after you eat.

13
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:07,920
Want some help?

14
00:02:11,020 --> 00:02:12,020
No, I'm good.

15
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:15,040
This is...

16
00:02:24,340 --> 00:02:25,780
This is all your fault, Sara-senpai.

17
00:02:27,820 --> 00:02:29,220
That's exactly why I'm helping you.

18
00:02:31,509 --> 00:02:35,803
But you still need to take your medicine.

19
00:02:40,150 --> 00:02:41,640
I don't think I can right now...

20
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:46,470
Let me just... calm down first.

21
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:17,690
What were you doing just now?

22
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:25,110
Next time you're not feeling well,

23
00:04:25,550 --> 00:04:26,790
you have to tell me right away.

24
00:04:30,450 --> 00:04:31,450
I'm fine.

25
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:34,010
I know I worried you this time,

26
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:36,190
but I'm used to handling things on my own.

27
00:04:41,340 --> 00:04:42,580
Well, you have me now.

28
00:04:46,530 --> 00:04:48,140
Will you always be by my side?

29
00:04:54,050 --> 00:04:55,050
Just kidding.

30
00:04:55,620 --> 00:04:56,620
Forget I said that.

31
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,120
Fu.

32
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:03,760
Just for tonight.

33
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:08,480
Just stay with me tonight.

34
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,040
I'll stay with you.

35
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:29,410
I'll be right here.

36
00:05:30,180 --> 00:05:31,530
Just focus on getting better.

37
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:50,500
"The Boy Next World My Destiny"
(Episode 5)

38
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:47,600
Morning.

39
00:06:53,090 --> 00:06:54,190
How's your cold?

40
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:55,860
Is your fever gone?

41
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:57,850
What are you talking about?

42
00:07:04,540 --> 00:07:05,740
And what's with that wound?

43
00:07:07,140 --> 00:07:08,140
Huh?

44
00:07:08,430 --> 00:07:09,590
You're acting really strange.

45
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:11,320
Fu...

46
00:07:13,523 --> 00:07:14,883
It's like he's a different person.

47
00:07:15,940 --> 00:07:16,940
Fu!

48
00:07:18,190 --> 00:07:19,440
Wait, we need to talk.

49
00:07:46,060 --> 00:07:47,180
How does it feel?

50
00:07:48,690 --> 00:07:49,690
What?

51
00:07:50,950 --> 00:07:53,070
How does it feel to
peek into a parallel world?

52
00:07:56,790 --> 00:07:57,870
What are you talking about?

53
00:07:58,730 --> 00:08:00,000
You have Fu with you.

54
00:08:03,403 --> 00:08:05,423
I once had a future with him, too.

55
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:12,110
Stop being such a coward.

56
00:08:23,890 --> 00:08:24,890
Not again...

57
00:08:36,170 --> 00:08:37,170
I'm sorry.

58
00:08:39,670 --> 00:08:41,670
I had that same dream again.

59
00:08:43,290 --> 00:08:44,610
That's why I wanted to believe...

60
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,730
that we really were a couple.

61
00:08:59,940 --> 00:09:01,470
Sorry, I'm just being selfish.

62
00:09:04,930 --> 00:09:06,730
I just don't want us to be strangers again.

63
00:09:34,770 --> 00:09:37,829
That last scene was so cool.

64
00:09:37,830 --> 00:09:39,739
And then the camera slowly pulls back...

65
00:09:39,740 --> 00:09:41,629
and then—bam!—that wide shot hits.

66
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:43,389
With the deep narration
and music, I was a mess.

67
00:09:43,413 --> 00:09:44,719
The teacher's gonna scold you.

68
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:47,820
Man, you're such a teacher's pet.

69
00:09:49,690 --> 00:09:50,690
Hey, wait!

70
00:09:52,212 --> 00:09:53,752
Hey! No running in the halls!

71
00:09:54,170 --> 00:09:55,170
Sorry!

72
00:09:55,530 --> 00:09:56,530
Give it back!

73
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,220
Hey, did you hear about the mock exam?

74
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:02,786
Someone got a perfect
score in every subject.

75
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:03,630
Sara-senpai?

76
00:10:03,830 --> 00:10:06,439
He's so perfect it's actually creepy.

77
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,999
Yeah, it's insane.

78
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,510
Hey, get back to sweeping.

79
00:10:11,420 --> 00:10:13,010
Oh, right. Sorry.

80
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:17,240
It's annoying because Fu works so hard.

81
00:10:18,425 --> 00:10:20,165
That's exactly what's so annoying.

82
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:20,860
What?

83
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,140
Maybe Senpai works hard too.

84
00:10:23,570 --> 00:10:25,690
You guys don't know anything, so shut up.

85
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:03,500
What were you doing?

86
00:11:07,350 --> 00:11:08,990
I'm making a paper cup phone.

87
00:11:10,230 --> 00:11:11,770
This way we can talk whenever we want.

88
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:26,560
Fu.

89
00:11:27,050 --> 00:11:28,210
I have something to tell you.

90
00:11:31,850 --> 00:11:32,850
What is it?

91
00:11:36,370 --> 00:11:37,370
Never mind.

92
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:41,240
What was that about?

93
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:46,960
Button.

94
00:12:07,620 --> 00:12:08,620
Shower.

95
00:12:09,410 --> 00:12:10,490
I need to go take a shower.

96
00:12:11,010 --> 00:12:12,040
I'm heading out.

97
00:12:17,530 --> 00:12:18,890
I'm just a substitute.

98
00:12:19,820 --> 00:12:21,090
Just a stand-in.

99
00:12:26,330 --> 00:12:30,840
Until Senpai goes back to his own world.

100
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:36,320
Didn't we buy way too much?

101
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,540
You just got over being sick.

102
00:12:38,650 --> 00:12:40,340
This is a bit much...

103
00:12:40,490 --> 00:12:41,130
It's fine.

104
00:12:41,131 --> 00:12:43,200
You need to eat a lot
to get your energy back.

105
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:45,800
So...

106
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:47,050
did you invite him?
No.

107
00:12:47,441 --> 00:12:49,080
He was already there when I got to Fu's.

108
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:03,100
Why was Sara-senpai at Fu's house?

109
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,379
He stayed over to take care of me.

110
00:13:05,380 --> 00:13:06,420
- He stayed over?!
- What?!

111
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:08,509
They live in the same building.

112
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:09,710
- The same building?!
- No way!

113
00:13:18,190 --> 00:13:18,490
Let's eat.

114
00:13:18,491 --> 00:13:20,589
- Let's eat.
- Which one should I pick?

115
00:13:20,590 --> 00:13:22,390
- I'll take that one.
- Which one?

116
00:13:23,190 --> 00:13:24,510
That one's fine. Anything's fine.

117
00:13:24,910 --> 00:13:25,910
Don't just throw it!

118
00:13:30,470 --> 00:13:32,070
So, did you guys finally do it?

119
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:33,320
Fu...

120
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:34,850
I'm so happy for you.

121
00:13:36,030 --> 00:13:37,170
What?

122
00:13:37,940 --> 00:13:39,940
Oh, so you didn't sleep in the same room.

123
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:46,090
Fu, you're so innocent
it's actually worrying.

124
00:13:47,710 --> 00:13:49,570
He's eating slower than usual.

125
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,900
He might not be fully recovered yet.

126
00:13:54,543 --> 00:13:55,963
Once Fu is feeling better,

127
00:13:57,030 --> 00:13:58,270
I'll explain everything to him.

128
00:14:12,630 --> 00:14:14,150
It's been a while since I've had rice.

129
00:14:14,590 --> 00:14:15,890
This is so good.

130
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:21,420
Is no one else hungry?

131
00:14:34,130 --> 00:14:35,130
Hey, Sara.

132
00:14:35,170 --> 00:14:36,650
I heard you went back home yesterday.

133
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:38,960
I was worried, man.

134
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:42,320
I thought you were being
held captive or something.

135
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:46,080
She told me not to see my dad.

136
00:14:47,870 --> 00:14:48,870
What?

137
00:14:49,210 --> 00:14:51,870
Didn't your dad go all
that way just to see you?

138
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:53,350
That robot old hag...

139
00:14:53,430 --> 00:14:54,880
she doesn't care at all.

140
00:14:54,940 --> 00:14:55,940
Is that all you have to say?

141
00:14:55,941 --> 00:14:57,010
Wait, don't hang up!

142
00:14:57,150 --> 00:14:59,020
For Friday's second period Finance class...

143
00:14:59,070 --> 00:15:00,910
the professor said your
attendance is too low.

144
00:15:01,560 --> 00:15:02,410
This week,

145
00:15:02,411 --> 00:15:04,280
you absolutely have to show up.

146
00:15:04,580 --> 00:15:05,580
Got it.

147
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,339
I actually got called in for that.

148
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:10,390
And I'm not even taking that class!

149
00:15:11,350 --> 00:15:12,949
You really need to make some friends

150
00:15:12,950 --> 00:15:14,730
other than me in your classes.

151
00:15:15,110 --> 00:15:16,310
Want to go see a movie?

152
00:15:20,950 --> 00:15:21,950
Who is this?

153
00:15:22,070 --> 00:15:23,750
There's a film festival I'm interested in.

154
00:15:24,270 --> 00:15:26,080
I thought you might like it, Taiga-senpai.

155
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:27,910
You're the one from...

156
00:15:29,660 --> 00:15:30,830
Why do you have his phone?

157
00:15:31,790 --> 00:15:33,529
I didn't want to hear Taiga-senpai nagging,

158
00:15:33,530 --> 00:15:34,980
so I just picked up.

159
00:15:35,540 --> 00:15:36,540
So, how about that movie?

160
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:39,120
Like I'd go with you.

161
00:15:47,773 --> 00:15:48,973
Do you think he'll say yes?

162
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:51,560
Ask him yourself.

163
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:56,150
Are you intentionally trying
not to think about anything?

164
00:15:59,170 --> 00:16:01,360
You were thinking so much
when you were with Fu.

165
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:06,990
If Taiga-senpai won't go,
I'll just have to ask Fu instead.

166
00:16:11,150 --> 00:16:12,920
Please don't even joke about that.

167
00:16:13,350 --> 00:16:14,780
I'll figure something out.

168
00:16:21,382 --> 00:16:23,702
What did Taiga-senpai say on the phone?

169
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:25,900
Oh.

170
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:29,530
He asked if I was okay after seeing my mom.

171
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:32,030
He's always worrying about nothing.

172
00:16:33,090 --> 00:16:34,880
Why would he be worried?

173
00:16:39,850 --> 00:16:41,020
My mom...

174
00:16:41,870 --> 00:16:43,680
she doesn't even see me as a human being.

175
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:51,260
What do you mean?

176
00:16:55,950 --> 00:16:57,090
When I was eight,

177
00:16:57,640 --> 00:16:59,020
my parents got divorced.

178
00:16:59,920 --> 00:17:01,020
My mom took me,

179
00:17:02,150 --> 00:17:03,810
and my brother stayed with my dad.

180
00:17:04,950 --> 00:17:06,050
You have a brother?

181
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,050
We don't see each other much.

182
00:17:12,570 --> 00:17:14,290
I don't want him getting dragged into this.

183
00:17:17,260 --> 00:17:18,400
Into what? With your mom?

184
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:26,570
I was always forced
to do nothing but study.

185
00:17:31,650 --> 00:17:32,650
Back in middle school,

186
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:35,310
Taiga and I made a plan

187
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:37,990
to skip school and go out.

188
00:17:39,430 --> 00:17:40,430
Yeah?

189
00:17:42,540 --> 00:17:43,540
That woman...

190
00:17:44,330 --> 00:17:46,240
she had her people beat me.

191
00:17:48,570 --> 00:17:49,970
Right in front of Taiga.

192
00:17:54,960 --> 00:17:56,840
"Don't think. Just obey."

193
00:17:59,890 --> 00:18:01,650
That's her favorite thing to say.

194
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:07,420
If you just take it all,

195
00:18:09,130 --> 00:18:11,140
life is easier if you just follow orders.

196
00:18:13,250 --> 00:18:14,810
That's how she forced me to see things.

197
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:27,440
Let's go.

198
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:36,199
(Arakawa Amusement Park)

199
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,680
Come on, let's go.

200
00:18:39,213 --> 00:18:40,213
Hurry up!

201
00:18:41,890 --> 00:18:43,450
No, that's not right. Like this.

202
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:46,440
There you go.

203
00:18:48,370 --> 00:18:49,550
I'm definitely not losing.

204
00:18:49,950 --> 00:18:50,990
I'm going to win for sure.

205
00:18:51,376 --> 00:18:53,136
- Is that how it works?
- Yeah.

206
00:18:53,340 --> 00:18:54,340
You have to teach me.

207
00:18:55,740 --> 00:18:57,400
Honestly...

208
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:58,770
Pay attention, okay?

209
00:18:59,970 --> 00:19:01,110
Thanks.

210
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:05,080
What's this?

211
00:19:05,810 --> 00:19:06,810
Open it and see.

212
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:14,760
Here.

213
00:19:15,580 --> 00:19:16,580
Are you sure?

214
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:18,390
It's for you.

215
00:19:22,020 --> 00:19:23,020
Thank you.

216
00:19:30,330 --> 00:19:31,330
Sara-senpai.

217
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:34,250
Sara-senpai!

218
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:35,300
You smiled!

219
00:19:45,490 --> 00:19:47,720
Hey, let's play again.

220
00:19:47,910 --> 00:19:48,810
One more time.

221
00:19:48,811 --> 00:19:50,410
Please? Just one more time.

222
00:19:51,580 --> 00:19:52,960
Sara-senpai, please!

223
00:19:53,380 --> 00:19:54,380
Just once more.

224
00:20:05,390 --> 00:20:06,950
We haven't ridden the dinosaur one yet.

225
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:12,720
We still need to go on
the dinosaur carousel.

226
00:20:14,370 --> 00:20:15,430
It's already closed.

227
00:20:18,190 --> 00:20:19,620
- Hey.
- Yeah?

228
00:20:20,780 --> 00:20:21,780
Let's go again.

229
00:20:22,980 --> 00:20:23,980
Again?

230
00:20:24,102 --> 00:20:26,252
Yeah, just one more time.

231
00:20:28,890 --> 00:20:29,890
One more time.

232
00:20:30,660 --> 00:20:31,460
One more time!

233
00:20:31,660 --> 00:20:33,940
One more time, one more time!

234
00:20:42,670 --> 00:20:43,670
Here.

235
00:20:44,140 --> 00:20:45,990
Wow, Sara-senpai, you're terrible at this.

236
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:47,960
Give it here.

237
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:49,460
Honestly, let me help you.

238
00:20:49,710 --> 00:20:51,140
Okay, here we go.

239
00:20:52,090 --> 00:20:53,520
See? You have to do it like this.

240
00:20:54,610 --> 00:20:55,630
Try again. There.

241
00:20:56,110 --> 00:20:57,110
You got it, you got it.

242
00:20:57,890 --> 00:20:58,890
We did it! We did it!

243
00:20:59,530 --> 00:21:00,610
Alpacas are so cute, right?

244
00:21:01,850 --> 00:21:02,850
Yeah.

245
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:04,240
Their faces are so long.

246
00:21:12,910 --> 00:21:13,910
Come on.

247
00:21:21,950 --> 00:21:23,990
Just touch the screen to start.

248
00:21:27,330 --> 00:21:28,330
Okay, get ready.

249
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:30,180
- Smile! Smile!
- We're taking the picture!

250
00:21:30,730 --> 00:21:33,300
Three, two, one!

251
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:37,730
This is how it turned out.

252
00:21:37,820 --> 00:21:39,370
Don't look so grumpy.

253
00:21:39,580 --> 00:21:41,170
Look at the camera and smile.

254
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:43,050
I am smiling.

255
00:21:43,980 --> 00:21:45,820
Your smile is way gentler
when you're with Fu.

256
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:49,720
Look, look! Strike a pose.

257
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:52,360
Three, two, one!

258
00:21:56,180 --> 00:21:57,590
This is how it turned out.

259
00:21:59,100 --> 00:22:00,300
Is this no good?

260
00:22:01,330 --> 00:22:03,030
It's not that it's no good...

261
00:22:03,040 --> 00:22:04,240
This next one is the last one.

262
00:22:06,850 --> 00:22:08,020
I actually like this one.

263
00:22:08,370 --> 00:22:10,620
Three, two, one!

264
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:21,440
Is this really your first
time taking sticker photos?

265
00:22:22,990 --> 00:22:23,990
I'm keeping this one.

266
00:22:24,660 --> 00:22:25,870
In exchange for that bear.

267
00:22:41,550 --> 00:22:42,550
Are you mad?

268
00:22:45,550 --> 00:22:46,550
I'm just shy.

269
00:22:57,380 --> 00:22:58,480
Did you have fun?

270
00:23:02,110 --> 00:23:03,430
It was the best day of my life.

271
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,560
You're Fu Yotsuba, right?

272
00:23:19,050 --> 00:23:22,140
Yes... Who are you?

273
00:23:24,260 --> 00:23:26,210
I'm an attendant for the Kogami family.

274
00:23:28,820 --> 00:23:30,680
His mother would like to know

275
00:23:31,540 --> 00:23:32,670
how much money it will take

276
00:23:33,860 --> 00:23:36,030
for you to disappear from her son's life.

277
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:54,400
(Career Preference Survey)

278
00:25:56,120 --> 00:25:57,120
You...

279
00:25:57,190 --> 00:25:59,290
Are you really going to
do what that old hag says?

280
00:26:05,990 --> 00:26:06,990
Taiga-senpai.

281
00:26:09,810 --> 00:26:11,546
